reviews.review_text: Bravo I like this concert and the recording quality is good.

Takes me way back This show takes me waaaay back to my high school days when we would cut class for the day and go out to the countryside and put as much powder up or nose's that we could. I can close my eye's and still see pigpen doing operator. Those were some day"s that i truly miss.Don't miss the powder at all though,it was the music i miss.

last stand in NY i was a college kid.  19 yrs old, and i met the GD band, specifically Bobby Weir at my school the week before this concert....we made out at intermission and he asked me to come to the following weekend concert in Capitol Theater Porchester, NY.  i went.  spent the weekend with him and the rest of the band, girls. roadies, fans etch.  Bob and I spent the nights with each other.  soooooo,  i do remember lots about this concert, dancing on stage the entire night in my hippie sweater.  RED.  The bands favorite color.  ?  at least it's been mine.  i loved being around the band, but when they left NY to return to California i did not go with.  instead three months later i quit college and went to live with my friends who had emigrated to Santa Cruz, CA.  what i beautiful world it was when hippies roamed the earth!!  i'm 67 yrs old now.  a lot changed but one thing always remained the same:  my love for the GD band.  MY HEART IS SO FULL OF LOVE FOR THEM, and it's no wonder i'm nothing at all like the people i meet or even my own family members!  i knew the greats.
